    <fr:tree show-metadata="true" numbered="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://mkiyoaki.github.io/respg/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>respg</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/respg/</fr:route><fr:title text="MPhil Individual Project">MPhil Individual Project</fr:title><fr:meta name="institution"><fr:link href="https://www.cam.ac.uk/" type="external">University of Cambridge</fr:link></fr:meta><fr:meta name="position">Nov 2025 - Present</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>Supervised by <fr:link href="https://andreasvlachos.github.io/" type="external">Prof. Andreas Vlachos</fr:link>, studying whether step-level mathematical verification is better modelled as discriminative inference than generation. The project compares encoder-based verifiers with decoder-based LLMs, analyses their verification representations, and tests intervention methods for reducing shortcut-driven failures.
